HorizonNet — vendored inference code
====================================

Vendored from https://github.com/sunset1995/HorizonNet @ commit c9a7df9
(c9a7df90fc8ef4611e415b933dd851ec0ca00efd), trimmed to the inference
essentials needed by roomestim:

  - model.py
  - misc/utils.py        (load_trained_model + helpers)
  - misc/post_proc.py    (layout post-processing)
  - misc/panostretch.py  (panorama coordinate helpers)

The vendored code is licensed under the MIT License, Copyright (c) 2019
Cheng Sun. The full license text is in ./LICENSE.

Pretrained WEIGHTS are NOT included in this repository and are NOT covered
by the MIT code license. They are downloaded on first use (see
roomestim/vision/checkpoints.py) and carry their own dataset-derived terms:

  - st3d  (resnet50_rnn__st3d): trained on the Structured3D research dataset.
  - zind  (resnet50_rnn__zind): trained on the Zillow Indoor Dataset (ZInD),
           whose Terms of Use are ACADEMIC / NON-COMMERCIAL and require
           explicit acceptance before download/use.

Users are responsible for complying with the license/terms of whichever
weights they choose to download.
